  "closed_at": "2016-06-03 23:15:57 UTC",
  "body": "I read this http://olafurpg.github.io/scalafmt/#scalafmtcreateshugediffs!, and wonder, is this something we must expect most of the time when comitting changes to Scala code?\r\nI understand that there will be lots of diffs the first time scalafmt does reformatting, but why should there be huge diffs later on?"
